  "prompt": "How are septums pierced?",
  "response": "Septum piercings are a popular form of body modification where the septum, the strip of skin and cartilage between the nostrils, is pierced. Here\u2019s a general overview of how the procedure is typically performed:\n\n### 1. **Consultation and Preparation**\n   - **Consultation:** Before the piercing, you\u2019ll usually have a consultation with the piercer to discuss placement, jewelry options, and aftercare.\n   - **Cleaning:** The piercer will clean the area around your septum to reduce the risk of infection.\n\n### 2. **Marking the Spot**\n   - The piercer will use a marker to indicate the exact spot where the piercing will be made. This is crucial to ensure the piercing is centered and placed correctly.\n\n### 3. **Clamping**\n   - A septum clamp may be used to hold the tissue steady and make the piercing process more precise. The clamp also helps to minimize pain by numbing the area slightly.\n\n### 4. **Piercing**\n   - The piercer will use a sterilized, hollow needle to pierce through the marked spot. The needle is usually inserted from one nostril to the other, passing through the thin strip of skin in the septum (the \"sweet spot\"), not the cartilage.\n\n### 5. **Inserting the Jewelry**\n   - Once the needle is through, the piercer will immediately insert the jewelry (commonly a circular barbell, septum clicker, or captive bead ring) through the hole.\n\n### 6. **Final Adjustments and Cleaning**\n   - The piercer will make sure the jewelry is properly seated and may give you instructions on how to adjust it if necessary. They will also clean the area again.\n\n### Aftercare Instructions\n   - **Cleaning:** You\u2019ll be advised to clean the piercing twice a day with a saline solution or a recommended cleanser.\n   - **Avoid Touching:** Try not to touch the piercing with dirty hands to prevent infection.\n   - **Healing Time:** The healing process typically takes 6-8 weeks, but it can vary depending on individual health and aftercare practices.\n\n### Pain and Healing\n   - **Pain Level:** The pain level is generally moderate and brief, often described as a quick pinch or pressure.\n   - **Healing:** Proper aftercare is essential to avoid complications like infection or migration of the piercing.\n\n### Things to Consider\n   - **Jewelry Quality:** Ensure the jewelry used is made from high-quality materials like surgical steel, titanium, or gold to prevent allergic reactions.\n   - **Professional Piercer:** Always choose a professional piercer with good reviews and proper certification to ensure the procedure is done safely and correctly.\n\nIf you\u2019re considering a septum piercing, make sure to do your research and follow all aftercare instructions to ensure a smooth healing process.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
